<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4163] CQL3 ALTER TABLE command causes NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4163</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To reproduce the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;./cqlsh --cql3&lt;br/&gt;
Connected to Test Cluster at localhost:9160.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;cqlsh 2.2.0 | Cassandra 1.1.0-rc1-SNAPSHOT | CQL spec 3.0.0 | Thrift protocol 19.30.0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Use HELP for help.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cqlsh&amp;gt; CREATE KEYSPACE test34 WITH strategy_class = &apos;org.apache.cassandra.locator.SimpleStrategy&apos; AND strategy_options:replication_factor=&apos;1&apos;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cqlsh&amp;gt; USE test34;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cqlsh:test34&amp;gt; CREATE TABLE users (&lt;br/&gt;
          ... password varchar,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... gender varchar,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... session_token varchar,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... state varchar,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... birth_year bigint,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... pk varchar,&lt;br/&gt;
          ... PRIMARY KEY (pk)&lt;br/&gt;
          ... );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cqlsh:test34&amp;gt; ALTER TABLE users ADD coupon_code varchar;&lt;br/&gt;
TSocket read 0 bytes&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;INFO 16:07:11,757 Cassandra version: 1.1.0-rc1-SNAPSHOT&lt;br/&gt;
INFO 16:07:11,757 Thrift API version: 19.30.0&lt;br/&gt;
INFO 16:07:11,758 CQL supported versions: 2.0.0,3.0.0-beta1 (default: 2.0.0)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
