        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.runTask(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:886)
        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.run(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:908)
        at java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:680)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13256951" author="thepaul" created="Wed, 18 Apr 2012 20:51:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix attached here; also broken up into 3 more concise chunks on the 4163 branch in my github. Link:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/thepaul/cassandra/tree/pending/4163&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://github.com/thepaul/cassandra/tree/pending/4163&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, in testing, I found that ALTER TABLE  ALTER TYPE still doesn&apos;t work, and ALTER TABLE WITH only works in some cases. Will need to make new tickets for those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13256957" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 18 Apr 2012 20:58:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nit: could we initialize properties to an empty map to avoid having to null-check it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13256959" author="thepaul" created="Wed, 18 Apr 2012 21:03:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could, in the grammar definition, but that attribute is only ever updated with an assignment, so the empty map would be consed for nothing. Hardly a big deal either way though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13256970" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 18 Apr 2012 21:17:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I don&apos;t see this as performance critical so I&apos;d rather go for cleanliness.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
